Descrizione√à an annual herbaceous plant high, usually from 30 to 80 cm. Has a stem angular, leaves tripalmatosette consist of segments rather linear long approximately 2-2,5 cm. The flowers are sparse and arranged in racemes in a large corn on the cob; have a vibrant blue-purple, and a particular form due to the sepal upper elongated and similar to a thin horn. This feature has determined the common name of the plant. The stamens are numerous and arranged in 5 series spiralled. The fruit is a small follicle glabrous or slightly hairy. The flowering period is between may and June.
